'''Ali Jasim Elaibi Al-Tameemi''' ({{langx|ar|علي جاسم لعيبي التميمي}}; born 20 January 2004) is an Iraqi professional [[Forward (association football)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Najma SC (Saudi Arabia)|Al-Najma]], on loan from {{Italian football updater|Como}} club [[Como 1907|Como]], and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

==Club career==
===Al-Karkh===
At 14 years old, Ali Jasim made his [[Iraqi Premier League]] debut for [[Al-Karkh SC|Al-Karkh]] against [[Al-Zawraa SC|Al-Zawraa]] on 3 November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/alkarkh.sport/posts/pfbid0oy9zX4hnvg9LzHYtzWA2gy7wTMMMoxSR1VQLQ7KGvTHWp6m8jpaHyLK5SNHHJXz8l|title=المكتب الاعلامي لنادي الكرخ الرياضي|last=Al-Qaisi|first=Ammar|publisher=Al-Karkh SC|date=6 November 2018|language=ar}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in the last round of the [[2018–19 Iraqi Premier League]] against [[Amanat Baghdad SC|Amanat Baghdad]] on 24 July 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shafaq.com/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%81%D9%88%D8%B2-%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%85-%D9%85%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A|title=تعادلان وفوز بختام مشوار دوري القدم العراقي|publisher=Shafaq|date=24 July 2019|language=ar}}</ref>

===Al-Shorta===
Ali Jasim joined the defending Iraqi Premier League champions [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]] during the [[2019–20 Al-Shorta SC season|2019–20]] season under coach [[Abdul-Ghani Shahad]], although the season was later abandoned due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Iraq|COVID-19 pandemic]]. He made his debut for Al-Shorta in the [[2020–21 Iraq FA Cup]], coming off the bench in a 5–0 win over [[Al-Khalis SC|Al-Khalis]] on 17 November 2020.<ref name="shorta">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/i/events/1305583020544602114|title=تفاصيل مباريات الشرطة في موسم 2020-2021|publisher=Al-Shorta SC|date=14 September 2020}}</ref> Under Serbian coach [[Aleksandar Ilić (footballer, born 1969)|Aleksandar Ilić]], Jasim made one start and eight substitute appearances in the [[2020–21 Iraqi Premier League]] as Al-Shorta finished in fourth place, and also reached the semi-finals of the [[Iraq FA Cup]].<ref name="shorta"/>

===Al-Kahrabaa===
On 28 December 2021, Jasim signed for [[Al-Kahrabaa SC|Al-Kahrabaa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://earthiq.news/archives/2621|title=نادي الكهرباء يضم لاعبين جدد لفريق الكرة|publisher=Earthiq|date=28 December 2021|language=ar}}</ref> Under coach [[Luay Salah]], Jasim scored four league goals in the [[2021–22 Iraqi Premier League|2021–22]] season and a further six in the [[2022–23 Iraqi Premier League|2022–23]] season, where Al-Kahrabaa finished in fifth place, the joint-highest league finish in their history which saw them qualify for the [[2023–24 AFC Cup|AFC Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=History beckons for AFC Cup 2023/24 contenders as final edition of popular competition kicks off|access-date=21 September 2023|date=15 September 2023|website=the-AFC.com|publisher=Asian Football Confederation|language=en|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_cup/news/history_beckons_for_afc_cup%E2%84%A2_202324_contenders_as_final_edition_of_popular_competition_kicks_off.html}}</ref> Jasim also helped Al-Kahrabaa reach the [[Iraq FA Cup]] final in [[2022 Iraq FA Cup final|2022]], playing the first 60 minutes of the final, which Al-Kahrabaa lost 2–1 to Jasim's former club Al-Karkh.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/iraqfa/posts/pfbid0tRwqTiZWfyqCJgsrAeBEJDGoognwkPr4uKY8RgMgoFV6VNpwwgjCMrjCsBhFhmdXl|title=تشكيلة المباراة النهائية لبطولة كأس العراق بين فريقي الكهرباء و الكر|publisher=[[Iraq Football Association]]|date=16 July 2022}}</ref>

After Jasim's impressive performances for the [[Iraq national under-20 football team|Iraq U-20]] team, Jasim was close to signing for [[K.A.A. Gent]] in [[Belgium]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/irakees-toptalent-op-weg-naar-gent-ik-blijf-sowieso-niet-in-irak-het-is-of-belgiea-of-37684809|title=IRAKEES TOPTALENT OP WEG NAAR GENT? "IK BLIJF SOWIESO NIET IN IRAK, HET IS OF BELGIË, OF..."|publisher=One Football|date=16 June 2023}}</ref> and also generated interest from Turkish clubs [[Trabzonspor]] and [[Antalyaspor]], according to journalist [[Fabrizio Romano]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/1143252/kaa-gent-hoopt-groot-irakees-talent-jassim-nog-te-overtuigen.html|title=Romano: 'KAA Gent geeft komst van Irakees toptalent Jassim nog niet op'|publisher=Voetbal Primeur|date=17 July 2023|language=nl}}</ref>

===Antalyaspor===
On 20 July 2023, Jasim officially signed a three-year contract with [[Süper Lig]] side Antalyaspor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.trthaber.com/haber/spor/antalyaspor-irakli-ali-jasimi-kadrosuna-katti-783004.html|publisher=TRT Haber|title=Antalyaspor Iraklı Ali Jasim'i kadrosuna kattı|date=20 July 2023}}</ref> However, Jasim terminated his contract by mutual consent after only two days at the club for personal reasons, and returned to Al-Kahrabaa in Iraq.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://antalyam.com/antalyaspor-ile-ali-jasimin-yollari-ayrildi/|publisher=Antalya AM|title=Antalyaspor ile Ali Jasim'in yolları ayrıldı|date=22 July 2023|access-date=14 October 2023|archive-date=20 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231020223249/https://antalyam.com/antalyaspor-ile-ali-jasimin-yollari-ayrildi/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sadeceantalyaspor.com/haber/sl/ali-jasim-ile-yollar-ayrildi.html|title=Ali Jasim İle Yollar Ayrıldı|date=22 July 2023}}</ref>

===Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya===
On 2 August 2023, Jasim signed for [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] on loan from [[Al-Kahrabaa SC|Al-Kahrabaa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%85-%D9%8A%D9%83%D8%B4%D9%81-%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%AA%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9|title=علي جاسم يكشف سبب اختياره القوة الجوية|date=2 August 2023|language=ar|publisher=Winwin}}</ref> He scored two goals on his debut in the [[2023–24 AFC Champions League]] group stage in a 2–2 draw against [[Sepahan S.C.|Sepahan]], and scored again in the next group match against [[FC AGMK|AGMK]] in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/group_c_air_force_club_irq_2-2_sepahan_fc_irn_1.html|title=Group C: Air Force Club (IRQ) 2-2 Sepahan FC (IRN)|publisher=The-AFC|date=18 September 2023}}</ref> This made him the youngest player in history to score three goals in one [[AFC Champions League]] season at 19 years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TheAFCCL/status/1712461883859685487|title=The youngest player to score 3 goals in an ACL season|publisher=AFC Champions League|date=12 October 2023}}</ref> He scored his fourth goal of the campaign in a 2–0 win over [[Saudi Pro League]] champions [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/group_c_air_force_club_irq_v_al_ittihad_fc_ksa_2.html|title=Group C: Air Force Club (IRQ) 2-0 Al Ittihad FC (KSA)|publisher=The-AFC|date=6 November 2023}}</ref>

===Como 1907===
On 24 July 2024, Jasim signed for newly promoted [[Serie A]] side [[Como 1907|Como]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |last=karma |date=2024-07-24 |title=Como 1907 secures signing of one Asia's biggest young talents: Ali Jasim |url=https://comofootball.com/en/como-1907-secures-signing-of-ali-jasim/ |access-date=2024-07-24 |website=Como 1907 |language=en-US}}</ref>

====Loan to Almere City====
On 28 January 2025, Jasim was loaned to [[Almere City]] in the Dutch [[Eredivisie|top tier]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Almere City|url=https://almerecity.nl/almere-city-1/irakees-international-ali-jasim-strijkt-neer-in-almere/|title=Irakees international Ali Jasim strijkt neer in Almere|trans-title=Iraqi international Ali Jasim settles in Almere|date=28 January 2025|access-date=28 January 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

====Loan to Al-Najma====
On 29 August 2025, Jasim joined [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Najma SC (Saudi Arabia)|Al-Najma]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=النجمة يضم العراقي علي جاسم |url=https://www.alyaum.com/article/6612816}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Jasim participated with the [[Iraq national under-20 football team|Iraq U-20]] team at the [[2023 AFC U-20 Asian Cup]]. Jasim scored the winning goal in the quarter-final against rivals [[Iran national under-20 football team|Iran]], which qualified Iraq for the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/national/afc_u20_asian_cup/news/this_is_the_best_goal_of_my_career_says_iraq%E2%80%99s_jasim.html|publisher=The-AFC|title=This is the best goal of my career, says Iraq's Jasim|date=12 March 2023}}</ref> Jasim scored again in the semi-final against [[Japan national under-20 football team|Japan]], which Iraq won on penalties to reach the final, with Jasim also scoring a penalty in the shootout. Iraq were beaten 1–0 by hosts [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|Uzbekistan]] in the final and thus took second place in the championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/how-iraq-qualified-for-the-2023-fifa-u-20-world-cup-against-all-odds|title=How Iraq qualified for the 2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup against all odds|publisher=FIFA.com|date=16 March 2023}}</ref>

Jasim participated in all three of Iraq's matches in the U-20 World Cup, where they lost 0–4 against [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]] and 0–3 against [[Tunisia national under-20 football team|Tunisia]], and drew 0–0 with [[England national under-20 football team|England]], thus being eliminated at the group stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socceriraq.net/2023/05/22/iraq-beaten-by-uruguay-in-u20-world-cup-opener/|title=Iraq beaten by Uruguay in U20 World Cup opener|publisher=Iraq National Team|date=22 May 2023|access-date=14 October 2023|archive-date=13 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240613172841/https://socceriraq.net/2023/05/22/iraq-beaten-by-uruguay-in-u20-world-cup-opener/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://socceriraq.net/2023/05/25/spirited-iraq-u20-side-suffer-3-0-defeat-to-tunisia/|title=Spirited Iraq U20 side suffer 3–0 defeat to Tunisia|publisher=Iraq National Team|date=25 May 2023|access-date=14 October 2023|archive-date=18 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518162332/https://socceriraq.net/2023/05/25/spirited-iraq-u20-side-suffer-3-0-defeat-to-tunisia/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 26 June 2024, Jasim was named in the [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq U-23]] team for the [[2024 Summer Olympics]] in Paris. Jasim came on as a sub in the maiden game against [[Ukraine Olympic football team|Ukraine]], to score the winner in the 75th minute.

===Senior===
Jasim made his debut for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] on 13 October 2023 in the [[2023 Jordan International Tournament|Jordan International Tournament]] against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/sport/%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D8%AC%D8%A8%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%AF%D8%AF-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D9%86|title=ودية قطر تجبر كاساس على إعادة حساباته... والوافدون الجدد يخطفون الأضواء|publisher=Al-Araby|language=ar|date=14 October 2023}}</ref>

